jokes: Why don’t skeletons fight each other? They don’t have the guts.
What do you call fake spaghetti? An impasta.
Why don’t programmers like nature? It has too many bugs.
How do you comfort a JavaScript bug? You console it.
Why did the coder bring a ladder to work? Because they wanted to scale the project.
Why do cows wear bells? Because their horns don’t work.
I told my wife she was drawing her eyebrows too high. She looked surprised.
Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field.
What’s orange and sounds like a parrot? A carrot.
I asked the librarian if the library had any books on suicide. She said they were all checked out.
I only know 25 letters of the alphabet. I don’t know y.
I used to play piano by ear, but now I use my hands.
I couldn’t figure out how to put my seatbelt on. Then it clicked.
I can’t believe I got fired from the calendar factory. All I did was take a day off.
How do you make a hormone? Don’t pay her.
I’m reading a book about anti-gravity. It’s impossible to put down.
I told my computer I needed a break, and now it won’t stop sending me Kit-Kats.
Why did the golfer bring two pairs of pants? In case he got a hole in one.
I have a fear of speed bumps. But I’m slowly getting over it.
I started a company selling land mines disguised as prayer mats. Prophets are going through the roof.
Parallel lines have so much in common. It’s a shame they’ll never meet.
I’m trying to lose weight, but it’s not working. I’m on a seafood diet. I see food and I eat it.
I’m terrible at math, but I can count on you.
Why don’t skeletons ever use cell phones? They don’t have the body for it.
I used to be a baker, but I couldn’t make enough dough.
I’m a big fan of whiteboards. They’re re-markable.
I don’t trust stairs. They’re always up to something.
I think I’m allergic to seafood. I break out in hives and catch crabs.
I bought some shoes from a drug dealer. I don’t know what he laced them with, but I’ve been tripping all day.
What did the grape do when it got stepped on? Nothing, it just let out a little wine.
